def add_mapping_based_on_reference_measure(df_forecast, df_hier_measure):
    df_forecast_mapping = df_measure.select("MeasureLevel7LongDescription", "BaseMeasureCode").join(F.broadcast(df_forecast), F.col("MeasureLevel7LongDescription") == F.col("reference_measure"))
    df_forecast_mapping = df_hier_measure.select("BaseMeasureCode", "Mapping").join(F.broadcast(df_forecast_mapping), on="BaseMeasureCode")
    return df_forecast_mapping

## Get Customers
Get all possible customers at the specified customer scope and level.

Get Customers

Get all possible customers at the specified customer scope and level.

from functools import reduce
from pyspark.sql import DataFrame

def get_customers_per_forecast(forecast, customer_data):

    # All the possible levels where a customer can be selected on
    possible_customer_levels = ['DistributionChannelCode', 'DivisionCode', 'GlobalCustomerBannerCode', 'GlobalCustomerBannerCodeName', 'GlobalCustomerBannerName', 'GlobalCustomerClusteringCode', 'GlobalCustomerClusteringCodeName', 'GlobalCustomerClusteringName', 'GlobalCustomerCode', 'GlobalCustomerCodeName', 'GlobalCustomerName', 'GlobalCustomerSK', 'GlobalCustomerTotalCode', 'GlobalCustomerTotalCodeName', 'GlobalCustomerTotalName', 'LocalClusterLevel1Code', 'LocalClusterLevel1CodeName', 'LocalClusterLevel1Name', 'LocalClusterLevel1Region', 'LocalClusterLevel2Code', 'LocalClusterLevel2CodeName', 'LocalClusterLevel2Name', 'LocalClusterLevel2Region', 'LocalClusterLevel3CodeName', 'LocalClusterLevel3Name', 'LocalClusterLevel3Region', 'LocalCustomerId', 'SalesOrganisationCode'] #'LocalClusterLevel3Code', 

    # Pivot forecast to contain all these columns
    forecast_pivot = forecast.groupBy("forecast_id").pivot("Customer Level", possible_customer_levels).agg(F.first("Customer")).cache()

    def get_customer_at_level(level):
        return (customer_data.select(level, "LocalClusterLevel3Code")
                    .join(F.broadcast(forecast_pivot), on=level, how="inner")
                    .withColumn("LocalClusterLevel3Code", F.split('LocalClusterLevel3Code', '_')[2])
                    .withColumn('local_customer_level_6_code', F.regexp_replace('LocalClusterLevel3Code', r"^[0]*", ""))
                    .select("forecast_id", "local_customer_level_6_code"))
                    

    # Join with customers
    customer_at_all_levels = [get_customer_at_level(level) for level in possible_customer_levels]
    customer_at_all_levels_union = reduce(DataFrame.unionAll, customer_at_all_levels)

    return customer_at_all_levels_union

## Get Products

Get Products

def get_products_per_forecast(forecast, product_df):

    # All the possible levels where a customer can be selected on
    possible_product_levels = ["SKUCode", "ProductCodeName", "CorporateBrandName", "BrandFormName",
                      "CorporateProductGroupName", "SegmentName", "MarketName", "CategoryName",
                      "CategoryGroupName", "TotalGlobalCategoryName"]

    
    # Pivot forecast to contain all these columns
    forecast_pivot = forecast.groupBy("forecast_id").pivot("Scope_Target", possible_product_levels).agg(F.first("Scope_Value")).cache()

    def get_product_at_level(level):
        return product_df.join(F.broadcast(forecast_pivot), on=level, how="inner").select("forecast_id", "GlobalProductSK")

    # # Join with customers
    product_at_all_levels = [get_product_at_level(level) for level in possible_product_levels]
    product_at_all_levels_union = reduce(DataFrame.unionAll, product_at_all_levels)

    return product_at_all_levels_union

## Calculate months based on "reference_window" and "reference_period"

Calculate months based on "reference_window" and "reference_period"

# Get YTD months
periods = {"H1": ["01", "02", "03", "04", "05", "06"],
           "H2": ["07", "08", "09", "10", "11", "12"],
           "Q1": ["01", "02", "03"],
           "Q2": ["04", "05", "06"],
           "Q3": ["07", "08", "09"],
           "Q4": ["10", "11", "12"]}

def months_for_reference_window_and_period(reference_window: str, reference_period: str) -> List[str]:
    year = reference_period[0:4]
    if reference_window == 'Year to date':
        months = [f"{year}{str(i).zfill(2)}" for i in range(1, int(reference_period[4:6])+1)]
    else:
        period = reference_period[4:6]
        if not period.isnumeric():
            months = [year + i for i in periods[period]]
        else:
            months = [reference_period]
    return months


print(months_for_reference_window_and_period("Year to date", "201208"))

# Make it a udf


months_for_reference_window_and_period_udf = F.udf(months_for_reference_window_and_period, ArrayType(StringType()))

def add_months_array_column_based_on_reference_period_and_window_column(df):
    return (df
                .withColumn("months", months_for_reference_window_and_period_udf("reference_window", "reference_period")))


t = add_months_array_column_based_on_reference_period_and_window_column(forecast_df_id)

# Get value using indirection
def add_value_using_indirection_on_mapping_column(df):
    #Use UDF to get correct value
    def indirection(f):
        f["reference_measure_value"] = None
        f["reference_measure_value"] = f.apply(lambda row : row[row.Mapping], axis=1)
        return f
    
    # Return Schema for UDF
    sc = copy.deepcopy(df.schema)
    sc.add(field="reference_measure_value", data_type=DoubleType())

    return (df
        .groupby("forecast_id")
        .applyInPandas(indirection, schema=sc)
        .drop(*[c for c in df.columns if c.startswith("cb_")])
        .where(F.col("reference_measure_value") > 0)
        )

    final_cols = ['sku_code',

## Get Actuals

Get Actuals

# Get actuals for GlobalProductSK, CustomerSK, yearmonth, BussinessUnitCode
 
 
def get_aggregated_measure_for_forecast(df_forecast, df_customer, df_product, df_actuals, df_hier_measure):
    customers = get_customers_per_forecast(df_forecast, df_customer)
    products = get_products_per_forecast(df_forecast, df_product)
    display(df_forecast)
 
 
    # Preprocessing on df_forecast
    df_forecast = df_forecast.drop("Mapping", "BaseMeasureCode").withColumnRenamed("Value", "value_to_allocate")
 
    # Get mapping of the reference_value
    df_forecast_mapping = add_mapping_based_on_reference_measure(df_forecast, df_hier_measure)
 
    # Calculate what months a forecast applies to using UDF
    df_forecast_months_array = add_months_array_column_based_on_reference_period_and_window_column(df_forecast_mapping)
    df_forecast_yearmonth = df_forecast_months_array.withColumn("yearmonth_forecast", F.explode("months")).withColumnRenamed("forecast_id", "forecast_id_from_forecast")
 
    # Join actuals on Products
    df_actuals_filtered_products = (df_actuals
            .join(F.broadcast(products), on="GlobalProductSK")
            .withColumn("local_customer_level_6_code", F.regexp_replace('local_customer_level_6_code',r"^[0]*", "")))
 
    # Join actuals on customers
    df_actuals_filtered_product_customer = df_actuals_filtered_products.drop("Mapping").join(F.broadcast(customers), on=["local_customer_level_6_code", "forecast_id"])
 
    df_forecast_for_actuals_filter = df_forecast_yearmonth.select("yearmonth_forecast", "GlobalBusinessUnitCode", "forecast_id_from_forecast", "Mapping", "value_to_allocate", 'PROMO_FLAG_:_Yes_/_No', "BaseMeasureCode", "Allocation_basis")
    
    df_actuals_filtered_all = (df_actuals_filtered_product_customer
            .join(F.broadcast(df_forecast_for_actuals_filter), (df_forecast_for_actuals_filter.yearmonth_forecast == df_actuals_filtered_product_customer.yearmonth) & (df_forecast_for_actuals_filter.GlobalBusinessUnitCode == df_actuals_filtered_product_customer.business_unit_code) & (df_forecast_for_actuals_filter.forecast_id_from_forecast == df_actuals_filtered_product_customer.forecast_id))
            #.drop("forecast_id_from_forecast")
            )
 
    df_actuals_filtered_with_reference_taken = add_value_using_indirection_on_mapping_column(df_actuals_filtered_all)
 
    # Aggregate over forecast
    partition = Window.partitionBy("forecast_id")
    df_actuals_total_over_measure = df_actuals_filtered_with_reference_taken.withColumn ("reference_measure_total",F.sum(F.col("reference_measure_value")).over(partition))
 
    # Allocate over forecast
    df_actuals_allocated = (df_actuals_total_over_measure
                               .withColumn('value', F.col("value_to_allocate") * F.col("reference_measure_value") / F.col("reference_measure_total")))
 
    # Fix output format
    print(df_actuals_allocated.columns)
    df_allocations_output = (df_actuals_allocated
                                 .withColumnRenamed("value_to_allocate", "Total_Amount_To_Allocate")
                                 .withColumnRenamed("BaseMeasureCode", "Measure")
                                 .withColumnRenamed("Comments", "comments")
                                 .withColumnRenamed("Scope_Target", "scope_target")
                                 .withColumnRenamed("Scope_Value", "scope_value")
                                 .withColumnRenamed("reference_measure_value", "ref_measure_value")
                                 .withColumn("Promo", F.upper(F.substring('PROMO_FLAG_:_Yes_/_No', 0,1))).drop("PROMO_FLAG_:_Yes_/_No")
                                 .withColumn("scenario_code", F.lit("FOR"))
                                 .withColumnRenamed("Fcst_Version", "scenario_version_code")
                                 .withColumnRenamed("Reason_code", "reason_code")
                                 .withColumnRenamed("Channel_Code", "channel_code")
                                 .withColumnRenamed("Allocation_basis", "driver_measure")
                                 #.drop("yearmonth_forecast")
                                 .withColumn("data_source", F.lit("Allocation_Notebook"))
                                 .withColumn("date_generated", F.current_timestamp())
                                 # Fix Types
                                 .withColumn('sku_code', F.regexp_replace('sku_code', r'^[0]*', '').cast(IntegerType()))
                                 .withColumn('local_customer_level_6_code',
                                   F.col('local_customer_level_6_code').cast(IntegerType()))
                                 .withColumn('scenario_version_code', F.col('scenario_version_code').cast(IntegerType()))
                                 .withColumn('yearmonth', F.col('yearmonth').cast(IntegerType()))
                            )
    display(df_allocations_output)
                       
    f = select_final_output_cols_of_allocation(df_allocations_output)
    return f
 
t = get_aggregated_measure_for_forecast(forecast_df_id, df_customer, df_product, df_actuals, df_hier_measure)
display(t)
